cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper discusses issues with up-sampling methods commonly used in generative convolutional deep neural networks, which are often used for image and video generation tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel regularization term for training optimization, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the detection of deepfakes, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
